<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-02-28</DATELINE><TITLE>A Call to Introduce Structured Zika Surveillance in India</TITLE><BODY>India has the climatic conditions conducive to year-round transmission of Zika virus, and a structured disease surveillance program should be implemented to prevent an outbreak. Such a program should (i) start screening before an outbreak arises; (ii) collect baseline data to assess future disease risk and monitor potential birth defects; and (iii) provide new insights into the ecology of the disease and inform public health policy following the one health concept.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>